Invoking: `validate` with `{'patch': '--- a/Modules/_cursesmodule.c\n+++ b/Modules/_cursesmodule.c\n@@ -3257,10 +3257,18 @@\n     if (initialised) {\n-        wrefresh(stdscr);\n-        return (PyObject *)PyCursesWindow_New(stdscr, NULL);\n+        if (stdscr == NULL) {\n+            PyErr_SetString(PyCursesError, catchall_NULL);\n+            return NULL;\n+        }\n+        wrefresh(stdscr);\n+        return (PyObject *)PyCursesWindow_New(stdscr, NULL);\n     }\n \n-    win = initscr();\n-\n-    if (win == NULL) {\n-        PyErr_SetString(PyCursesError, catchall_NULL);\n-        return NULL;\n-    }\n+    win = initscr();\n+    if (win == NULL || stdscr == NULL) {\n+        PyErr_SetString(PyCursesError, catchall_NULL);\n+        return NULL;\n+    }\n'}`
responded: The previous patch only checked for `stdscr == NULL` in the `initialised` branch, but the sanitizer report now points to a null dereference at line 3262, which is `win = initscr();`. This means that after calling `initscr()`, the returned pointer `win` may be NULL, and the code must not use `stdscr` or `win` if this happens.

However, the code already checks `if (win == NULL)` and returns an error. But, crucially, the code later uses `win` to create the window object, but it does not check if `stdscr` is NULL after `initscr()`. In some curses implementations, `stdscr` is set by `initscr()`, but it is not guaranteed by the C standard that `stdscr` will be non-NULL if `initscr()` returns non-NULL. So, we must check both `win` and `stdscr` after `initscr()`.

**Correct fix:**
- After `win = initscr();`, check if either `win == NULL` or `stdscr == NULL`. If either is NULL, raise an error and return NULL.
- In the `initialised` branch, also check if `stdscr == NULL` before using it.

Here is the patch:

```diff
--- a/Modules/_cursesmodule.c
+++ b/Modules/_cursesmodule.c
@@ -3257,10 +3257,18 @@
     if (initialised) {
-        wrefresh(stdscr);
-        return (PyObject *)PyCursesWindow_New(stdscr, NULL);
+        if (stdscr == NULL) {
+            PyErr_SetString(PyCursesError, catchall_NULL);
+            return NULL;
+        }
+        wrefresh(stdscr);
+        return (PyObject *)PyCursesWindow_New(stdscr, NULL);
     }

-    win = initscr();
-
-    if (win == NULL) {
-        PyErr_SetString(PyCursesError, catchall_NULL);
-        return NULL;
-    }
+    win = initscr();
+    if (win == NULL || stdscr == NULL) {
+        PyErr_SetString(PyCursesError, catchall_NULL);
+        return NULL;
+    }
```

